text: Lancaster County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2020 census, the population was 322,608, making it the second-most populous county in Nebraska. Its county seat is Lincoln, the state capital. The county was created in 1859. Lancaster County is part of the Lincoln, NE Metropolitan Statistical Area. == References == Category:Nebraska counties Category:1850s establishments in Nebraska Territory Category:1859 establishments in the United States
